E Yonge Son If\nr ou need their services\ni r\nw\ny trY I E lONE t SON\niljf\nr J i Plumbers Ocala Fit\niL\nJ i\nIf I\ntt I OCALA PRESSIKfi CLUB p I\nJ F WILLIAMSON Prop I\nr c a I\nRates reasonable All Goods pressed I\n41j and Cleaned en Short Motive and De I\ntr\ni fevered Promptly I\ni 4 All transient work not called for\nw t wIthin 30 days will be sold for charges I\nll\n5 STlHcIYER i MACAY\ni If FUNERAL DIRECTORS\n1t\n1t\ni Undertakers and Embalmers I\nlast i\nW D E McIVER ALFRED E OWEtfl\nu Undertakers\nt Fine Caskets and Burial Robes I\nAll Work Done by Licensed Em\nr\ns balmers and Fully Guaranteed 1\nl\n1\n0\nit I\nilce lIce IceJ I i\n1 i I\nr r\nt QUALITY RIGHT I\nI\nDELIVERY RIGHT I\nrr\nJi PRICE i RIGHT\nWr IFL01IDA PACKING ICE CO I\nof j\nit BENJAMIN IN CHARGE II\ni 1 I I\nI\nI\ny 7 1T n T1n\nr r L n L E X J DE i\nt1 i I I\nJlif Practical\nlJZi\nf t CARPENTER AND BUILDER\n1\nit iafefull estimates made on all contract\nA1T or hives more and better work fa\nr i rieY than arty other contractor\nI s l\nMX fr r 1 J fM 1c S lt i\nr 1bv\nn\nt J4 o t\nF\nI\nI\nFins OF FIOW\n1\nContinued From tprst Page\nI\nI I\nA Very High Average\ni I\nI I would like to call your attention to I\nv i\nI the marvelous record of the banks of\ni\nI the United States for 1907 There were\n1 in operation twentyfour thousand\nseven hundred and eightythree banks\nwith eightynine failures What other\nMines of business could show such a\nI small percentage of loss under the ex\ntraordinary conditions that existed\nI While there have be n sporadic cases\nof malfeasance in conduct of banks\nI the tremendous weight of the testi\nmony developed by the experience of\nforty years or more shows that the\nhanker is first of all an honest man\ni\nt that he knows his duty and does it\nI that he is held in esteem by his neigh\nI hors What city or town will you go\n1 into ynd not find a banker holding\nsome office of honor or trust Numbers\nI of banks that have clod down during\nI the cast three months will resume bus\nIness This would not be possible had\ni not their affairs been honestly admin\nistered\nI The average annual rate of loss from\nfailures of national banks for the past\ni thirty years is eight hundredths\nI of one per cent It is safe to say that\njinks of other descriptions would show\nan equally favorably proportion\nI Business Outlook is Brightening\nLooking over the field of general bus\niness in our state we find a strong\ntendency toward improvement New I\nand extensive beds of phosphate rock i\nhave been discovered new plants for\nthe mining of the rock are constantly\nbeing erected prices are better than\nfor several years past the turpentine\nand lumber industries while not yield i\ning the remunerative prices of two\nI\nyears ago are nevertheless being\nbrought into satisfactory conditions\nthrough more economical manage k\nr\nment the growth of1 tobacco under ar\ntificial shade in the Quincy section has\nbecome a great source of revenue and\nis rapidly being extended the socall\ned backbone section running from\nGainesville to Dade City has been\nfound particularly well adapted fto the\ngrowth of early vegetables cantaloupes I\nand watermelons large sums were re\nturned to the farmers of Alachua and\nMarion counties last season through\nthe sale of the cantaloupe crop alone\nthe farmers of SumtjHv county are\nmeeting with great success in the cul\ntivation of cucumbers lislngr irrigation\ni\nagainst drought and l tte frost the\ngrowth of celery has become a regular\nI industry in Orange county the field of\nI orange growing is being extended in\nI South Florida An encouraging feature\nI s in our agricultural industries is the ad\nvance in uptodate methods in culti\nI\nvation the use of irrigation and labor\nI saving machinery the Intensive sys\ntern is growing in favor thE canning\nfactory is also beginning to appear to\ntake over the surplus of the vegetable\ncrop after shipments have ceased a\nnew and wonderful attraction for tour\nists have been added to those we al\nready have by the completion of the\nFlorida East Coast Rallwat to Knights\nKey the influx of winter visitors is\ngreater than ever You have an object\nlesson in the attractive city of our\nhosts We as bankers are vitally in\nterested in all this It is our duty to i\nso shape our course that we can afford\nI\nthe greatest help to the greatest num\nber in developing the resources of our i\nstate\nMy predecessors for the past two\nyears have lectured you on the neces\nsity of going slow on loans If the ex\nperience of strenuous November was\nnot a sufficient object lesson a lecture\nfrom me would be like whistling down\nI\nthe wind\nIn conclusion I will ask you to dili I\ngently use your influence as plain\nAmerican citizens to see to it that good\nand proper men are sent to represent\nus in the halls of legislation Ve need i\nconstructive not destructive legisla 1 I\ntion Send the demagogues to the rear j\nAs an association we have no favors to\nask in the way of legislation we simply\nwant justice j\nT thank you for the honor your have I\nconferred on me in electing me as your\ni\npresiding officer I will endeavor to\nshow my appreciation by continuing I\nin the year tiXcome to strive for the\nI\nupbuilding of our association J\ni\nWANTS IT KNOWN\n1\nPeter L Durisoe the Conner trucker\nwishes it known that he will visit Ocala\nThursday instead of Friday with a I\nwagon load of fine fresh vegetables I\nI i\nBABY HANDS I\nI\nWill got into mischief often it j\nI Weans a burn or cut or scald Apply II\nRu Hards Snow Liniment just as soon j\ns the nceident happens and the pain i\nvill be relieved while the wound will\nheal quickly and nicely A sure cure\nI or sprains rheumatism and all pains I\nTrice 25c 50c and 1 a bottle Sold\nI by the AntiMonopoly Drug Store\nr\nr\nI I\nANOTHER WOMAN AVENGER\nCharles M Sanford a Wealthy Brook\nlyn Lawyer Shot Down by a\nWoman He Wronged\nI I Xov York Feb 26Miss Jennie I\nI Bunt shot and seriously wounded Chas j\ni M Sanford a wealthy and prominent i\nlawyer in his Brooklyn office yester\ni day in revenge she alleges for ruin\nI ing her life Miss Bunt waited until 1\nSanford appeared at his office and then\nj fer a brief talk in private shot him in\nthe back of the head He Is too crit\nI i ally wounded to make a statement\nI but she is raving in the police station\nI cf her wrongs and is apparently de\nmerited\nI\n1\nNEGLECTED COLDS\nTHREATEN LIFE\nI\nFrom the Chicago Tribune\nDont trifle with a cole is good\nj deice for prudent men and women\nI It may be vital i the case of a child\nI Proper food good ventilation and dry\nj warm clothing are the proper safe\nguards against colds If they are\nI\ni maintained through the changeable\nt\nweather of autumn winter and\nj pring the chances of a surprise from\nordinary colds will be slight But the\ni\nordinary light cold will become severe\ni If neglected and a well established\nripe cold Is to the germs of diphtheria\nwhat honey is to the be The great\nest menace to chila lite at this season\nof the year Is the neglected cold\nWhether it Is a child or adult the cold\nslight or severe the very best treat\nment that can be adopted Is to give\nChqjnberlairVs Cough Remedy It is\nsafe and sure The great popularity\nand immense sale of this preparation\nhas been attained by its remarkable I\ncures of this ailment A cold never\nexults in pneumonia when it is given\nFor sale by all drugglits\nWEALTHY CHINAMAN WOUNDED\nI\nBy a Burglar who had a Lively Pistol\nBattle for the Boodle\nNew York Feb 26A H Foon who\nis said to be New Yorks richest China\nman was shot as he lay in bed last\nnight and his physicians say he can\nnot live It is rumored In Chinatown\nthat this shooting means the beginning\nof another long war but the police\nthink it is probable that a thief did the\nshooting as the Chinam had sev\neral thousand dollars in his room Be\nfore Foon fell wounded he engaged in\na pistol duel with the intruder who\nescaped\nTH